    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - June 1, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🏰 Lebanon ceasefire meets the castle tour\n\nThe ceasefire in Lebanon is now doing that modern diplomatic trick where it exists mostly as a word everyone says while moving artillery.\n\n- **The escalation:** AP says Israel ordered strikes on Beirut's southern suburbs after troops reached their deepest point in Lebanon in 26 years and Hezbollah fired toward northern Israel, including near Haifa.\n- **The map:** Israel seized the Beaufort Castle area in southern Lebanon; AP puts Lebanese deaths since March 2 above 3,300, with about 1 million displaced.\n- **The talks:** Direct Israel-Lebanon talks are due in Washington, while Hezbollah says it will not accept results it does not control.\n\n*This is less a ceasefire than a calendar invite with airstrikes attached.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/lebanon-israel-hezbollah-netanyahu-dahiyeh-rubio-ceasefire-airstrikes-a4708d5ed8d75f74463ba88c1cabca33) | [AP](https://apnews.com/article/45d86ee821798e88d8e0c82576ca4558)\n\n---\n\n## 🛢️ Ukraine keeps auditing Russian oil\n\nKyiv's sanctions policy has become very literal: if the refinery funds the war, send the spreadsheet by drone.\n\n- **The strike:** Ukraine said it hit Rosneft's Saratov refinery about 700 kilometers from the front line, causing a large fire; Russia reported civilian infrastructure damage.\n- **The reach:** AP says Ukraine also claimed strikes on a Rostov fuel depot and the Lazarevo pumping station in Kirov, more than 1,200 kilometers from Ukrainian-controlled land.\n- **The output:** Reuters calculations show Russian diesel production fell about 10% in May after another 10% drop in April as refineries cut or halted output.\n\n*Russia wanted strategic depth. Ukraine found the fuel tanks inside it.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/russia-ukraine-war-drones-nuclear-plant-4168345770d6d3a3808ba9dcb9dc3305) | [Reuters](https://www.globalbankingandfinance.com/russias-diesel-output-falls-10-drone-attacks-data-analysis/)\n\n---\n\n## 🚨 The Iran ceasefire gets louder\n\nThe U.S.-Iran ceasefire is holding in the same way a cracked windshield holds: technically, while everyone accelerates.\n\n- **The exchange:** AP says the U.S. bombed Iranian radar and drone sites after Iran shot down an American drone; Tehran then targeted U.S. troops in Kuwait with missiles that Washington says were intercepted.\n- **The choke point:** AP reports only 36 ships crossed Hormuz in the seven days to Friday, compared with more than 130 per day before the war.\n- **The diplomacy:** Reuters says Iran halted indirect talks after Israel pushed deeper into Lebanon; oil rose more than $5 a barrel after the report.\n\n*Negotiations continue, if by negotiations we mean missiles with footnotes.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/iran-us-irael-war-kuwait-strikes-88daa9f90b48baaa7beb18e35515c59d) | [Reuters](https://www.investing.com/news/world-news/us-says-it-struck-iranian-military-sites-tehran-responds-with-air-base-attack-4718003)"
  }
]
